			<h3>What we strive to do</h3>
			<p>We believe STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics) education starts at home. We strive to:</p>  
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Inspire</strong> interest in building and creating</li>
				<li><strong>Teach</strong> children innovator skills of observing, questioning, experimenting, and critical thinking</li> 
				<li><strong>Make it easier</strong> by packaging up everything needed each month</li>
				<li><strong>Waste not</strong> by creating projects around the best existing building and software platforms</li>  
			</ul>

			<h3>What's in a Project Kit?</h3>
			<p>Each month you will receive a UCanBe Project Kit with all the raw materials, toy parts, teaching moments, and instructions needed for a fun, foundational STEM project. Each project can be assembled in under 90 minutes, and can be re-configured and re-deployed in multiple ways, wherever your imagination takes you. We have 3 criteria when designing a Project Kit:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Is it fun and cool? If it races, explodes, combusts, accelerates, crashes, or oozes, and turns kids into creators & innovators, then it’s fun and cool.</li>
				<li>Does it teach you core STEM principles that you can apply in real life?</li>
				<li>Can it be re-used for ongoing and iterative learning?</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="alert alert-warning"><strong>Important Note:</strong> To get started, you will need a Base Kit, purchased separately. The Base Kit has the foundational components you will need for your Project Kits within your chosen field of learning and learning platform (eg, electrical engineering using the LittleBits building platform). As you grow with us, you will need different Base Kits for different learning platforms. Think of the Base Kit as the necessary skeleton and the UCanBe boxes as the flesh and muscles.</p>

