			<h3>Why Start with Electronics?</h3>
			<p>Electronics (making things work using a power source) is our first Learning Theme. Electronic engineering is critical in some of today's most exciting new inventions, like GPS and electric power generation. Besides being super fun and cool, electronics engineering introduces many core STEM principles: energy sources, circuits, motion & velocity, friction, geometry, and much more. <%= link_to "UCanBe Electronics", subscribe_path %> program challenges students to design and build circuits that can power “on” anything they imagine, starting with a Smart Car.</p> 

			<h3>Who is this product for?</h3>
			<p>Everyone. But best for elementary age children, 6 - 12. We all have an intrinsic curiosity about how things work. Just as toddlers loves blocks and kids loves Legos; designing and building are key components of play. UCanBe is the next step for kids who want to create and bring learning to life. No prior expertise is necessary. If you are already a budding engineer, UCanBe provides Challenges to confound and inspire you.</p>
